{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The new me is beauty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":3000,"text":"Yeah, people used to say, \"Norman's OK,"},{"time":8000,"text":"but if you followed what he said, everything would be usable"},{"time":10000,"text":"but it would be ugly.\""},{"time":12000,"text":"Well, I didn't have that in mind, so ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"This is neat."},{"time":19000,"text":"Thank you for setting up my display."},{"time":21000,"text":"I mean, it's just wonderful."},{"time":23000,"text":"And I haven't the slightest idea of what it does or what it's good for,"},{"time":26000,"text":"but I want it."},{"time":28000,"text":"And that's my new life."},{"time":30000,"text":"My new life is trying to understand what beauty is about,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and \"pretty,\" and \"emotions.\""},{"time":36000,"text":"The new me is all about making things kind of neat and fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"And so this is a Philippe Starck juicer, produced by Alessi."},{"time":44000,"text":"It's just neat; it's fun. It's so much fun I have it in my house --"},{"time":48720,"text":"but I have it in the entryway, I don't use it to make juice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53720,"text":"In fact, I bought the gold-plated special edition"},{"time":57720,"text":"and it comes with a little slip of paper"},{"time":59720,"text":"that says, \"Don't use this juicer to make juice.\""},{"time":62720,"text":"The acid will ruin the gold plating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66720,"text":"So actually, I took a carton of orange juice"},{"time":68720,"text":"and I poured it in the glass to take this picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73720,"text":"Beneath it is a wonderful knife."},{"time":75720,"text":"It's a Global cutting knife made in Japan."},{"time":78720,"text":"First of all, look at the shape -- it's just wonderful to look at."},{"time":82920,"text":"Second of all, it's really beautifully balanced:"},{"time":85920,"text":"it holds well, it feels well."},{"time":87320,"text":"And third of all, it's so sharp, it just cuts."},{"time":89320,"text":"It's a delight to use."},{"time":91320,"text":"And so it's got everything, right?"},{"time":93320,"text":"It's beautiful and it's functional."},{"time":95320,"text":"And I can tell you stories about it,"},{"time":97320,"text":"which makes it reflective,"},{"time":99320,"text":"and so you'll see I have a theory of emotion."},{"time":101320,"text":"And those are the three components."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103320,"text":"Hiroshi Ishii and his group at the MIT Media Lab"},{"time":106320,"text":"took a ping-pong table and placed a projector above it,"},{"time":109320,"text":"and on the ping-pong table they projected an image of water"},{"time":112320,"text":"with fish swimming in it."},{"time":114320,"text":"And as you play ping-pong, whenever the ball hits part of the table,"},{"time":117320,"text":"the ripples spread out and the fish run away."},{"time":119320,"text":"But of course, then the ball hits the other side,"},{"time":121320,"text":"the ripples hit the -- poor fish, they can't find any peace and quiet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":125320,"text":"Is that a good way to play ping-pong?"},{"time":127320,"text":"No. But is it fun?"},{"time":129320,"text":"Yeah! Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132320,"text":"Or look at Google."},{"time":134320,"text":"If you type in, oh say, \"emotion and design,\""},{"time":139320,"text":"you get 10 pages of results."},{"time":141320,"text":"So Google just took their logo and they spread it out."},{"time":144320,"text":"Instead of saying, \"You got 73,000 results."},{"time":146320,"text":"This is one through 20. Next,\""},{"time":148320,"text":"they just give you as many o's as there are pages."},{"time":150360,"text":"It's really simple and subtle."},{"time":152360,"text":"I bet a lot of you have seen it and never noticed it."},{"time":155360,"text":"That's the subconscious mind"},{"time":157360,"text":"that sort of notices it -- it probably is kind of pleasant"},{"time":159360,"text":"and you didn't know why."},{"time":161360,"text":"And it's just clever."},{"time":163360,"text":"And of course, what's especially good is,"},{"time":165360,"text":"if you type \"design and emotion,\""},{"time":167360,"text":"the first response out of those 10 pages is my website."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173360,"text":"Now, the weird thing is Google lies,"},{"time":176360,"text":"because if I type \"design and emotion,\""},{"time":178360,"text":"it says, \"You don't need the 'and.' We do it anyway.\""},{"time":181360,"text":"So, OK."},{"time":183360,"text":"So I type \"design emotion\""},{"time":185360,"text":"and my website wasn't first again."},{"time":187360,"text":"It was third."},{"time":189360,"text":"Oh well, different story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192080,"text":"There was this wonderful review in The New York Times"},{"time":195080,"text":"about the MINI Cooper automobile."},{"time":197080,"text":"It said, \"You know, this is a car that has lots of faults."},{"time":200360,"text":"Buy it anyway."},{"time":202360,"text":"It's so much fun to drive.\""},{"time":204360,"text":"And if you look at the inside of the car --"},{"time":207360,"text":"I mean, I loved it, I wanted to see it, I rented it,"},{"time":209360,"text":"this is me taking a picture while my son is driving --"},{"time":212360,"text":"and the inside of the car, the whole design is fun."},{"time":215360,"text":"It's round, it's neat."},{"time":217360,"text":"The controls work wonderfully."},{"time":219360,"text":"So that's my new life; it's all about fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222360,"text":"I really have the feeling that pleasant things work better,"},{"time":225360,"text":"and that never made any sense to me"},{"time":228360,"text":"until I finally figured out -- look ..."},{"time":232360,"text":"I'm going to put a plank on the ground."},{"time":234360,"text":"So, imagine I have a plank about two feet wide and 30 feet long"},{"time":237360,"text":"and I'm going to walk on it, and you see I can walk on it without looking,"},{"time":240360,"text":"I can go back and forth and I can jump up and down."},{"time":242360,"text":"No problem."},{"time":244360,"text":"Now I'm going to put the plank 300 feet in the air --"},{"time":248360,"text":"and I'm not going to go near it, thank you."},{"time":253640,"text":"Intense fear paralyzes you."},{"time":255640,"text":"It actually affects the way the brain works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258640,"text":"So, Paul Saffo, before his talk said that he didn't really have it down"},{"time":262640,"text":"until just a few days or hours before the talk,"},{"time":264640,"text":"and that anxiety was really helpful in causing him to focus."},{"time":268640,"text":"That's what fear and anxiety does;"},{"time":270640,"text":"it causes you to be -- what's called depth-first processing --"},{"time":273640,"text":"to focus, not be distracted."},{"time":276640,"text":"And I couldn't force myself across that."},{"time":279640,"text":"Now some people can -- circus workers, steel workers."},{"time":282640,"text":"But it really changes the way you think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284640,"text":"And then, a psychologist, Alice Isen,"},{"time":287640,"text":"did this wonderful experiment."},{"time":289640,"text":"She brought students in to solve problems."},{"time":291640,"text":"So, she'd bring people into the room,"},{"time":293640,"text":"and there'd be a string hanging down here"},{"time":295640,"text":"and a string hanging down here."},{"time":297640,"text":"It was an empty room, except for a table with a bunch of crap on it --"},{"time":300640,"text":"some papers and scissors and stuff."},{"time":302640,"text":"And she'd bring them in,"},{"time":304640,"text":"and she'd say,"},{"time":306640,"text":"\"This is an IQ test and it determines how well you do in life."},{"time":309640,"text":"Would you tie those two strings together?\""},{"time":312640,"text":"So they'd take one string and they'd pull it over here"},{"time":315640,"text":"and they couldn't reach the other string."},{"time":318640,"text":"Still can't reach it."},{"time":320640,"text":"And, basically, none of them could solve it."},{"time":323640,"text":"You bring in a second group of people,"},{"time":326640,"text":"and you say, \"Oh, before we start,"},{"time":329640,"text":"I got this box of candy, and I don't eat candy."},{"time":332640,"text":"Would you like the box of candy?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":334640,"text":"And turns out they liked it, and it made them happy --"},{"time":337640,"text":"not very happy, but a little bit of happy."},{"time":339640,"text":"And guess what -- they solved the problem."},{"time":341640,"text":"And it turns out that when you're anxious"},{"time":344640,"text":"you squirt neural transmitters in the brain, which focuses you"},{"time":347640,"text":"makes you depth-first."},{"time":349640,"text":"And when you're happy -- what we call positive valence --"},{"time":352640,"text":"you squirt dopamine into the prefrontal lobes,"},{"time":354640,"text":"which makes you a breadth-first problem solver:"},{"time":356640,"text":"you're more susceptible to interruption; you do out-of-the-box thinking."},{"time":359640,"text":"That's what brainstorming is about, right?"},{"time":362640,"text":"With brainstorming we make you happy, we play games,"},{"time":365640,"text":"and we say, \"No criticism,\""},{"time":367640,"text":"and you get all these weird, neat ideas."},{"time":369640,"text":"But in fact, if that's how you always were you'd never get any work done"},{"time":372640,"text":"because you'd be working along and say, \"Oh, I got a new way of doing it.\""},{"time":375640,"text":"So to get work done, you've got to set a deadline, right?"},{"time":379640,"text":"You've got be anxious."},{"time":381640,"text":"The brain works differently"},{"time":383640,"text":"if you're happy. Things work better because you're more creative."},{"time":386640,"text":"You get a little problem, you say, \"Ah, I'll figure it out.\""},{"time":389640,"text":"No big deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391640,"text":"There's something I call the visceral level of processing, and there will be visceral-level design."},{"time":395080,"text":"Biology -- we have co-adapted through biology to\nlike bright colors."},{"time":399080,"text":"That's especially good that mammals and primates like fruits"},{"time":403080,"text":"and bright plants, because you eat the fruit"},{"time":405080,"text":"and you thereby spread the seed."},{"time":407080,"text":"There's an amazing amount of stuff that's built into the brain."},{"time":410080,"text":"We dislike bitter tastes, we dislike loud sounds,"},{"time":413080,"text":"we dislike hot temperatures, cold temperatures."},{"time":415080,"text":"We dislike scolding voices. We dislike frowning faces;"},{"time":419080,"text":"we like symmetrical faces, etc., etc."},{"time":423480,"text":"So that's the visceral level."},{"time":425480,"text":"In design, you can express visceral in lots of ways,"},{"time":428480,"text":"like the choice of type fonts and the red for hot, exciting."},{"time":433480,"text":"Or the 1963 Jaguar:"},{"time":435480,"text":"It's actually a crummy car, falls apart all the time,"},{"time":438480,"text":"but the owners love it."},{"time":440480,"text":"And it's beautiful -- it's in the Museum of Modern Art."},{"time":442480,"text":"A water bottle:"},{"time":444480,"text":"You buy it because of the bottle, not because of the water."},{"time":447480,"text":"And when people are finished, they don't throw it away."},{"time":450480,"text":"They keep it for -- you know, it's like the old wine bottles, you keep it for decoration"},{"time":453480,"text":"or maybe fill it with water again, which proves it's not the water."},{"time":456480,"text":"It's all about the visceral experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461200,"text":"The middle level of processing is the behavioral level"},{"time":465200,"text":"and that's actually where most of our stuff gets done."},{"time":467200,"text":"Visceral is subconscious, you're unaware of it."},{"time":469200,"text":"Behavioral is subconscious, you're unaware of it."},{"time":472200,"text":"Almost everything we do is subconscious."},{"time":474200,"text":"I'm walking around the stage -- I'm not attending to the control of my legs."},{"time":478200,"text":"I'm doing a lot; most of my talk is subconscious;"},{"time":481200,"text":"it has been rehearsed and thought about a lot."},{"time":483200,"text":"Most of what we do is subconscious."},{"time":485200,"text":"Automatic behavior -- skilled behavior -- is subconscious,"},{"time":488200,"text":"controlled by the behavioral side."},{"time":490200,"text":"And behavioral design is all about feeling in control,"},{"time":494200,"text":"which includes usability, understanding --"},{"time":497200,"text":"but also the feel and heft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499200,"text":"That's why the Global knives are so neat."},{"time":501200,"text":"They're so nicely balanced, so sharp,"},{"time":503200,"text":"that you really feel you're in control of the cutting."},{"time":505200,"text":"Or, just driving a high-performance sports car"},{"time":508280,"text":"over a demanding curb --"},{"time":510280,"text":"again, feeling that you are in complete control of the environment."},{"time":513280,"text":"Or the sensual feeling."},{"time":515280,"text":"This is a Kohler shower, a waterfall shower,"},{"time":517280,"text":"and actually, all those knobs beneath are also showerheads."},{"time":520280,"text":"It will squirt you all around"},{"time":522280,"text":"and you can stay in that shower for hours --"},{"time":524280,"text":"and not waste water, by the way,"},{"time":526280,"text":"because it recirculates the same dirty water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531280,"text":"Or this -- this is a really neat teapot I found"},{"time":533280,"text":"at high tea at The Four Seasons Hotel in Chicago."},{"time":537280,"text":"It's a Ronnefeldt tilting teapot."},{"time":539280,"text":"That's kind of what the teapot looks like"},{"time":541280,"text":"but the way you use it is you lay it on its back,"},{"time":545560,"text":"and you put tea in,"},{"time":547560,"text":"and then you fill it with water."},{"time":549560,"text":"The water then seeps over the tea."},{"time":552560,"text":"And the tea is sitting in this stuff to the right --"},{"time":555560,"text":"the tea is to the right of this line."},{"time":557560,"text":"There's a little ledge inside, so the tea is sitting there"},{"time":559560,"text":"and the water is filling it up like that."},{"time":561560,"text":"And when the tea is ready, or almost ready, you tilt it."},{"time":564560,"text":"And that means the tea is partially covered"},{"time":567560,"text":"while it completes the brewing."},{"time":569560,"text":"And when it's finished, you put it vertically,"},{"time":571560,"text":"and now the tea is -- you remember -- above this line"},{"time":573560,"text":"and the water only comes to here --"},{"time":576560,"text":"and so it keeps the tea out."},{"time":578560,"text":"On top of that, it communicates,"},{"time":580560,"text":"which is what emotion does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582560,"text":"Emotion is all about acting; emotion is really about acting."},{"time":585560,"text":"It's being safe in the world."},{"time":587560,"text":"Cognition is about understanding the world, emotion is about interpreting it --"},{"time":591560,"text":"saying good, bad, safe, dangerous,"},{"time":593560,"text":"and getting us ready to act, which is why the muscles tense or relax."},{"time":596560,"text":"And that's why we can tell the emotion of somebody else --"},{"time":600560,"text":"because their muscles are acting, subconsciously,"},{"time":602560,"text":"except that we've evolved to make the facial muscles really rich with emotion."},{"time":608560,"text":"Well, this has emotions if you like,"},{"time":610560,"text":"because it signals the waiter that, \"Hey, I'm finished. See -- upright.\""},{"time":614560,"text":"And the waiter can come by and say, \"Would you like more water?\""},{"time":617560,"text":"It's kind of neat. What a wonderful design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619560,"text":"And the third level is reflective,"},{"time":623560,"text":"which is, if you like the superego,"},{"time":627560,"text":"it's a little part of the brain that has no control over what you do,"},{"time":630560,"text":"no control over the -- doesn't see the senses,"},{"time":634560,"text":"doesn't control the muscles."},{"time":636560,"text":"It looks over what's going on."},{"time":638560,"text":"It's that little voice in your head"},{"time":640560,"text":"that's watching and saying, \"That's good. That's bad.\""},{"time":642560,"text":"Or, \"Why are you doing that? I don't understand.\""},{"time":644560,"text":"It's that little voice in your head that's the seat of consciousness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648080,"text":"Here's a great reflective product."},{"time":651080,"text":"Owners of the Hummer have said, \"You know I've owned many cars in my life --"},{"time":655080,"text":"all sorts of exotic cars,"},{"time":657080,"text":"but never have I had a car that attracted so much attention.\""},{"time":661680,"text":"It's about attention. It's about their image,"},{"time":666760,"text":"not about the car."},{"time":668760,"text":"If you want a more positive model --"},{"time":670760,"text":"this is the GM car."},{"time":672760,"text":"And the reason you might buy it now is because you care about the environment."},{"time":674760,"text":"And you'll buy it to protect the environment,"},{"time":676760,"text":"even though the first few cars are going to be really expensive"},{"time":679760,"text":"and not perfected."},{"time":681760,"text":"But that's reflective design as well."},{"time":683760,"text":"Or an expensive watch, so you can impress people --"},{"time":685760,"text":"\"Oh gee, I didn't know you had that watch.\""},{"time":688760,"text":"As opposed to this one,"},{"time":690760,"text":"which is a pure behavioral watch,"},{"time":692760,"text":"which probably keeps better time than the $13,000 watch I just showed you."},{"time":695760,"text":"But it's ugly."},{"time":697760,"text":"This is a clear Don Norman watch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699760,"text":"And what's neat is sometimes you pit one emotion against the other,"},{"time":702760,"text":"the visceral fear of falling"},{"time":705760,"text":"against the reflective state saying, \"It's OK. It's OK. It's safe. It's safe.\""},{"time":710760,"text":"If that amusement park were rusty and falling apart, you'd never go on the ride."},{"time":714760,"text":"So, it's pitting one against the other."},{"time":719840,"text":"The other neat thing ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":726840,"text":"So Jake Cress is this furniture maker,"},{"time":729840,"text":"and he makes this unbelievable set of furniture."},{"time":732840,"text":"And this is his chair with claw,"},{"time":734840,"text":"and the poor little chair has lost its ball"},{"time":737840,"text":"and it's trying to get it back before anybody notices."},{"time":741840,"text":"And what's so neat about it is how you accept that story."},{"time":745840,"text":"And that's what's nice about emotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748840,"text":"So that's the new me."},{"time":750840,"text":"I'm only saying positive things from now on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":753840,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}